Module com.example.protrack
Package com.example.protrack.report

Interface Report

All Known Implementing Classes:
OrgReport, UserReport
public interface Report
The Report interface defines methods for generating various reports related to work orders and production metrics.

  • Method Details

    • forecastWorkOrderChartValues

      Map<Double,Double> forecastWorkOrderChartValues()
      Maps each work order to its forecasted completion time and actual completion time. This data can be used to create a line chart comparing production against expected production.
      Returns:
      a map where keys represent normalized time values, and values represent forecasted and actual completion times.

    • calculateOrdersExpectedCycleTimeChartValues

      Map<Double,Double> calculateOrdersExpectedCycleTimeChartValues()
      Calculates the expected cycle times for work orders. This data can be used for cumulative area charts or burndown charts.
      Returns:
      a map where keys represent normalized time values, and values represent expected cycle times for work orders.

    • calculateOrdersActualCycleTimeChartValues

      Map<Double,Double> calculateOrdersActualCycleTimeChartValues()
      Calculates the actual cycle times for work orders.
      Returns:
      a map where keys represent normalized time values, and values represent actual cycle times for work orders.

    • calculateThroughputChartValues

      Map<Double,Double> calculateThroughputChartValues()
      Calculates the throughput of completed production over time. This data can be represented in a line chart.
      Returns:
      a map where keys represent normalized time values, and values represent throughput values for work orders.

    • calculateOnScheduleRate

      Double calculateOnScheduleRate()
      Calculates the on-schedule rate of work orders, indicating the percentage of orders that were completed on or before their due dates.
      Returns:
      the on-schedule rate as a percentage of completed work orders.

    • calculateTotalOrdersByStatus

      Map<String,Integer> calculateTotalOrdersByStatus()
      Calculates the total number of work orders by their status.
      Returns:
      a map where keys represent order statuses and values represent the count of work orders for each status.

    • calculateTotalOrders

      Integer calculateTotalOrders()
      Calculates the total number of work orders.
      Returns:
      the total number of work orders.

    • calculateTotalProductsProduced

      Integer calculateTotalProductsProduced()
      Calculates the total number of products produced across all work orders.
      Returns:
      the total number of products produced.

    • calculateTotalPartsUsed

      Integer calculateTotalPartsUsed()
      Calculates the total number of parts used across all work orders.
      Returns:
      the total number of parts used.

    • calculateTotalProductionCost

      Double calculateTotalProductionCost()
      Calculates the total production cost for all work orders.
      Returns:
      the total production cost as a double value.
